<subSubSection id="2A4332D3E863DBE7A2B11C41FB8CDAFB" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="3911E3DE310361C8186F488C36773DAA" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
<taxonomicName id="9BB6F3B5AFD6B6812EE308145653FA86" LSID="4696CABA-B05C-574E-A5F2-5A86C2F31358" authority="Emery, 1869" authorityName="Emery" authorityYear="1869" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Temnothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Temnothorax rogeri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="rogeri">Temnothorax rogeri Emery, 1869</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ED884792D560FAC7AE8D0D3C64B802CB" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2DDA47048827ACA48E6D440F678E986A" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D5BF82E2499E5E404BADD330998418F3" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
New record: South Pirin Mt., Kalimantsi vill., 10.05.-01.06.2002, 01-22.06.2002, 06.08-08.09.2002, pitfall traps, 8 w., leg. M. Langourov. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="199B09943F49931275E0903260AC5EDE" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EFD6B04B30A5C6B7BA02A5D071A49679" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph id="1FA1234B61B2F519C2B92245CAAFBAA7" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D21B6F233A3203E4ABC2567B53D3742" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
First record for Bulgaria. 
<taxonomicName id="74BACAEE1A67E843FD575CD035520AE9" authority="Mayr, 1861" authorityName="Emery" authorityYear="1869" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Temnothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Temnothorax rogeri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="rogeri">
<emphasis id="92C2F79FB31D0A4462B91DD5DFCE8DBC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Temnothorax rogeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an eastern Mediterranean species, known from Croatia, Greece, Montenegro and Turkish Thrace (
<bibRefCitation id="A5C9E5EB5359D5463989DB9B0909C483" author="Borowiec, L." journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Silesiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="1 - 22" refId="B7725669" refString="Borowiec, L., Salata, S., 2018. New records of ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Epirus, Greece. Acta Entomologica Silesiana 26: 1 - 22" title="New records of ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Epirus, Greece" volume="26" year="2018">Borowiec and Salata 2018</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="28793E18738C60E73271029FD73BF38E" author="Kiran, K." journalOrPublisher="Zoosystema" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="285 - 329" refId="B7725795" refString="Kiran, K., Karaman, C., 2020. Additions to the ant fauna of Turkey (Hymenoptera, Formicidae). Zoosystema 42 (18): 285 - 329" title="Additions to the ant fauna of Turkey (Hymenoptera, Formicidae)" volume="42" year="2020">Kiran and Karaman 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Recently, it was recorded in Slovakia, but most likely this record is based on an introduced specimen (
<bibRefCitation id="307DA8F4BD07050E55D8A43DDAD61AE2" author="Klesniakova, M." journalOrPublisher="Spixiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination=": 110" refId="B7725813" refString="Klesniakova, M., Pavlikova, A., Holecova, M., 2018. Temnothorax rogeri (Emery, 1869) becoming an established neozoon in Central Europe? (Hymenoptera, Formicidae). Spixiana 41 (1): 110" title="Temnothorax rogeri (Emery, 1869) becoming an established neozoon in Central Europe? (Hymenoptera, Formicidae)" volume="41" year="2018">
<normalizedToken id="AF85684D8C67817C593628AD9752464D" originalValue="Klesniaková">Klesniakova</normalizedToken>
et al. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). Morphologically, it is very close to 
<taxonomicName id="A715CBC9CC3A3105F8D68B8E13D455B5" genus="T." lsidName="T. recedens" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" rank="species" species="recedens">
<emphasis id="DBD01B75B68317EB867B7F7BF6962FA8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">T. recedens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nylander, 1856), which is known from the southern regions and the Black Sea coast in Bulgaria (
<bibRefCitation id="BBBE9416BD6EB2234235032C84D37146" author="Atanassov, N." journalOrPublisher="Bulgarian Academy of Sciences, Sofia" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7725616" refString="Atanassov, N., Dlussky, G. M., 1992. Fauna Bulgarica. 22. Hymenoptera, Formicidae. Bulgarian Academy of Sciences, Sofia" title="Fauna Bulgarica. 22. Hymenoptera, Formicidae" year="1992">Atanassov and Dlussky 1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="FEBFB7DB843F8CFE36F6F54B1CC80145" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="1 - 124" refId="B7725831" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Antonova, V., Radchenko, A. G., Atanasova, M., 2010. Catalogue of the ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) of Bulgaria. ZooKeys 62: 1 - 124" title="Catalogue of the ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) of Bulgaria" volume="62" year="2010">Lapeva-Gjonova et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
